Under 1.6.6 (and previous releases) when viewing changeset within Fisheye, an orange note would show up to each revision naming the review(s) that the change was part of. This made it very easy to spot which changes don't yet have reviews.

Under 2.0 this indicator is gone, you have to manually click the gear icon for the tools drop down to see if there is a review for the change. There is no way to tell just by glancing at the change.
{quote}
In Crucible 2.0.1 and 2.0.2, you have to click on a file then click on the revisions tab to see if it has a review. It would be useful to have a page to show a quick glance to see which changesets have a review or not.

If you have commited large text files such as large xml files, which have a long history, not only will it cause performance issues such as [FE-1088|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/FE-1088], you can get 

